column1: # Title: CSP Grid Interconnection Costs by ReEDS Region; CSP Class; and Bin

# Comments: These costs are the additional cost in $/MW (2004 USD) for interconnecting to the grid on top of the capital and OM costs. Costs are sometimes assigned at an arbitrary high value for region-class-bin combinations where no resource exists. Note that we need to apply an FCR to these interconnection costs.
# Source: Information based on ReEDS version 2017.  Files provided by ReEDS team in April 2017.
